snippet.textDisplay: This is straight-up a scam. It's similar to how you turn counter-fit money into real money. For example, take a fake $10 note and use it to buy something at a store, get the change back. There you have it fake into real. They are taking drug money using it to buy phones and reselling them. It's essentially double laundering. It's also why parts come from so many different areas of the world. Spread out the laundering so it's harder to track exactly where it all went.
